<!doctype html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><meta name="theme-color" content="#07111f"><title>Free Math Tools — Beyond Math</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="/beyond-math/assets/css/style.css?v=2.1"></head><body class="tools-page"><header class="site-header"><a class="brand" href="/beyond-math/"><span>Beyond Math <b>Tools</b></span></a><nav class="nav"><a href="/beyond-math/">Home</a><a href="/beyond-math/academy.php">Free lessons</a></nav></header><main class="section-pad tools-shell"><p class="eyebrow">Free · No login required</p><h1>Calculator tools</h1><p class="muted">A lightweight set of everyday math tools. More graphing and worksheet features are coming through Beyond ID.</p><section class="calculator-card" id="scientific"><label for="expression">Enter an expression</label><div class="calc-row"><input id="expression" inputmode="decimal" placeholder="Example: (12 * 4) + 8 / 2"><button id="calculate" class="btn primary" type="button">Calculate</button></div><output id="result" aria-live="polite">Result appears here</output><p class="privacy-note">Supported: numbers, +, −, ×, ÷, parentheses, decimals and percentages.</p></section><div class="tools-grid"><article id="fractions"><h2>Fraction helper</h2><p>Convert common fractions and decimals.</p><a href="/beyond-math/academy.php">Open lesson</a></article><article id="geometry"><h2>Geometry formulas</h2><p>Area, perimeter, volume and measurement references.</p><a href="/beyond-math/academy.php">Open formulas</a></article><article id="converter"><h2>Unit converter</h2><p>Length, mass, temperature and everyday measurements.</p><a href="/beyond-math/academy.php">Open converter lesson</a></article></div></main><script>const input=document.getElementById('expression'),result=document.getElementById('result');document.getElementById('calculate').addEventListener('click',()=>{let v=input.value.trim().replace(/×/g,'*').replace(/÷/g,'/').replace(/(\d+(?:\.\d+)?)%/g,'($1/100)');if(!v||!/^[0-9+\-*/().\s]+$/.test(v)){result.textContent='Use numbers and standard math operators only.';return;}try{const n=Function('"use strict";return ('+v+')')();result.textContent=Number.isFinite(n)?String(Math.round((n+Number.EPSILON)*1e10)/1e10):'Unable to calculate.';}catch(e){result.textContent='Check the expression and try again.';}});</script><script src="/assets/js/visitor-analytics.js" defer></script></body></html>
